{title: Ode To The Little Shack Out Back}
{artist: Bobby Bare}
{composer: Written by Billy Ed Wheeler}

[G]They passed an ordinance in the town
They said we'd have to tear it down
That little old shack out back so dear to [D7]me
Though the [G]health department said its day was [C]over and dead
It will [G]stand forever [D7]in my memo[G]ry
Don't let them tear that little brown building down
Don't let them [D7]tear that precious [G]building down
Don't let them tear that dear old [C]building [Am]down
There's [G]not another [C]like it in the [D7]country or the [G]town
It was not so long ago that I went tripping through the snow
Out to that house behind my old hound [D7]dog
Where I [G]would sit me down to rest like a [C]snowbird on his nest
And I'd [G]read that Sears and [D7]Roebuck [G]catalog
Oh I would hum a happy tune peeping through the quarter moon
As my daddy's kin had done so much [D7]before
It was [G]in that quiet spot daily [C]cares could be forgot
And it [G]gave the same [D7]relief to rich and [G]poor
repeat #2
Now it was not a castle fair but I could dream of future there
Build my castle to the yellow jackets [D7]drone
I could [G]orbit round the sun fight with [C]General Washington
Or [G]be a king [D7]upon a golden [G]throne
It wasn't fancy built at all we had newspapers on the wall
It was air-conditioned in the winter[D7]time
Oh it was [G]just an humble hut but its [C]door was never shut
And a [G]man could get [D7]inside without a [G]dime
repeat #2